The other prologues are for the most part spoken by a special Prologus and consist of long intro- ductions to the action of the play, varied by rather heavy witticisms. A few are spoken by mythological personageS, Mercurius (Amph.), Arcturus (Rud.); the Lar Fami· liaris is the speaker in the Aul. and Auxilium in the Cist.
